<br>
Once you have the kit, put one point in tailoring at your guild.  Then go kill a LOT of spiderlings.  Good sources of spiderlings are East Commons near Inn 1, the Steamfont Mountains druid ring, and Everfrost outside Halas.<br>
<br>
Collect the spiderling silks, and start by combining two at a time to make silk thread.  Hang onto the thread.  Once this trivials at 15, you can start combining two threads at a time to make silk bandages.  You can also combine two SPIDER (not spiderling) silks to make a silk swatch.<br>
<br>
Once you're at about 21, which I think is when the bandages become trivial, try some patchwork or raw silk armor.  For this you need patterns and pelts (or swatches for silk).  Ruined pelts work for patchwork -- I don't think you can use high quality pelts.  Wolf pelts make small, Cat pelts make medium, bear pelts make large.  You can sell the armor back to a vendor, or (what I generally do) hand it to nekkid newbies at the West Gate in FP.<br>
<br>
